The paper deals with the design and implementation of a distributed query engine for temporal property graphs, which involves database systems (cs.DB), data structures (cs.DS), and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of path queries for exploring graphs, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper focuses on temporal graphs, which are a specific type of graph with time-varying properties, making it relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
